Dear Team,
As part of the SCD compliance activity, the parameter net.ipv4.ip_forward was reviewed on the registry server <SERVER_HOSTNAME>.
It has been observed that Podman container networking is configured and actively used on this server. The server is using bridge/container network interfaces for registry and container communication.
The following outputs confirm the dependency:
podman network ls
ip route
ip a | grep -i podman
Disabling IP forwarding by setting:
net.ipv4.ip_forward = 0
impacts container communication, registry accessibility, and Podman network functionality.
Hence, the current configuration:
net.ipv4.ip_forward = 1
is required for application/container networking dependency and operational functionality of the server.
Requesting exception/waiver approval for this observation for the mentioned server.